17/08/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Clashes broke out between police and employees of the central Athens branch of the local Emporiki Bank on Tuesday (16 August). 
According to local media reports, the scuffles erupted after riot police tried to stop protesters from forcibly entering the offices of the bank, whose management was holding a meeting. 
Workers in Greece's banks called another strike Tuesday, to protest the latest changes to the pension laws. 
(Kathimerini - 17/08/05; ANA - 16/08/05)
